{
  "text": "This paper aimed to assess the congenital blind children cognition in relation to cognitive valence, planning and proposing a computerized process as a whole and not just as statistical analysis. The use of the laboratory Orange Canvas allowed not only standardized evaluation, but also a prognostic assessment, which enables, depending on the prognosis confirmation, a cognitive disabilities classification that have influenced in the child's performance, as reported by [CITATION_1] by claiming that CAS may indicate Disorder Attention Deficit Hyperactivity Disorder (ADHD). This allows a more objective and effective treatment, besides allowing the advance in the Planned Codes subtest administration as a whole, an administration fully computerized to automate the application and evaluation of subtest.",
